    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix TMGI Mobile Identity spare bits encoding/decoding\n\n### Summary\nThe TMGI mobile identity encoding and decoding functions had incorrect handling of spare bits. The decode function was extracting spare bits with an incorrect mask, and the encode function was not properly initializing the spare field. This caused inconsistent behavior when processing TMGI identities.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/MobileIdentity.c`: \n  - Fixed mask in `decode_tmgi_mobile_identity()` from `& 0x2` to `& 0x3` for proper 2-bit spare field extraction\n  - Added explicit spare field initialization in `encode_tmgi_mobile_identity()` \n  - Removed unnecessary bit masking operations\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/MobileIdentity.h`: No changes needed, structure definition was correct\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen processing TMGI mobile identities with non-zero spare bits, the decode function would incorrectly parse the spare field value, causing validation to fail even when the spare bits were properly set to 0. This resulted in `TLV_ENCODE_VALUE_DOESNT_MATCH` errors during mobile identity processing.\n\nThe issue can be observed when handling MBMS session establishment procedures where TMGI identities are exchanged between the UE and network.\n"
}